Considerar diversas fontes, fazer correlações, interpretar, hierarquizar: complexidade objetiva e subjetiva que só o ser humano pode fazer                        Big data is the term for a collection of data sets so large and complex that it becomes difficult to process using on-hand database management tools or traditional data processing applications. 
The challenges (desafios) include capture, curation (tratar), storage, search, sharing, transfer, analysis, and visualization. 
The trend to larger data sets is due to the additional information derivable from analysis of a single large set of related data, as compared to separate smaller sets with the same total amount of data, allowing correlations to be found to "spot business trends, determine quality of research, prevent diseases, link legal citations, combat crime, and determine real-time roadway traffic conditions.”           Earthscope é o maior projeto de ciência. Rastrear a evolução geologica da América do Norte, este observatório grava dados 3.8 milhões de milhas quadradas, com 67 terabytes de dados. Analisa ocorrências sismicas. (http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/44363598/ns/technology_and_science-future_of_technology/#.TmetOdQ--uI)
